<%= content_for :title, "Privacy Policy - MedGemma Health" %>
<%= content_for :meta_description, "MedGemma Health Privacy Policy outlining how we collect, use, and protect your personal and health information." %>

<!-- Hero Section -->
<section class="pt-32 pb-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 to-blue-50">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12" data-controller="fade-in">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 bg-blue-100 rounded-full mb-6">
        <i class="fas fa-shield-alt text-blue-600 mr-2"></i>
        <span class="text-sm font-medium text-blue-800">Legal</span>
      </div>
      
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
        Privacy 
        <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-indigo-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
          Policy
        </span>
      </h1>
      
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">
        Last Updated: May 23, 2025
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Policy Content -->
<section class="py-16 bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-blue max-w-none" data-controller="fade-in">
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          MedGemma Health ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our services, website, and mobile application.
        </p>
        <p>
          We take the protection of your personal and health information seriously and adhere to all applicable privacy laws, including the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA), General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), and the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA).
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Information We Collect</h2>
        
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Personal Information</h3>
        <p>We may collect personal information that you provide directly to us, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Contact information (name, email address, phone number, postal address)</li>
          <li>Account credentials (username and password)</li>
          <li>Payment information (credit card details, billing address)</li>
          <li>Demographic information (age, gender, location)</li>
          <li>User preferences and settings</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">Health Information</h3>
        <p>As a healthcare service provider, we collect protected health information (PHI), including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Medical history and records</li>
          <li>Symptoms and conditions</li>
          <li>Diagnostic information</li>
          <li>Treatment information</li>
          <li>Healthcare provider information</li>
          <li>Insurance information</li>
          <li>Medical images and documents you upload</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 mt-6">Automatically Collected Information</h3>
        <p>When you use our services, we may automatically collect certain information, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Device information (device type, operating system, browser type)</li>
          <li>IP address and network information</li>
          <li>Usage data (pages visited, features used, time spent)</li>
          <li>Location information (with your consent)</li>
          <li>Cookies and similar tracking technologies</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use your information for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>To provide and maintain our services</li>
          <li>To process and fulfill your requests, such as scheduling consultations</li>
          <li>To perform AI-powered diagnostic analysis and provide healthcare recommendations</li>
          <li>To communicate with you about our services, updates, and support</li>
          <li>To personalize your experience and improve our services</li>
          <li>To process payments and manage billing</li>
          <li>To ensure the security and integrity of our platform</li>
          <li>To comply with legal obligations and healthcare regulations</li>
          <li>For research and analytics purposes, using de-identified or aggregated data</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Sharing Your Information</h2>
        <p>We may share your information with the following parties:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Healthcare Providers:</strong> We share your health information with healthcare providers involved in your care.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Service Providers:</strong> We engage trusted third parties to perform services on our behalf, such as hosting, billing, analytics, and customer support.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Insurance Companies:</strong> With your authorization, we may share information with your insurance company for payment purposes.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> We may disclose information when required by law, regulation, legal process, or governmental request.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of the transaction.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not sell your personal information to third parties for marketing or advertising purposes.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement robust security measures to protect your information, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>End-to-end encryption for all data transmission</li>
          <li>Secure storage with advanced encryption standards</li>
          <li>Regular security assessments and audits</li>
          <li>Access controls and authentication mechanisms</li>
          <li>Employee training on privacy and security practices</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          While we take significant steps to protect your information, no system is completely secure. We continuously work to improve our security practices.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Your Privacy Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your information, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Right to access and receive a copy of your information</li>
          <li>Right to correct inaccurate information</li>
          <li>Right to delete your information</li>
          <li>Right to restrict or object to processing</li>
          <li>Right to data portability</li>
          <li>Right to withdraw consent</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise these rights, please contact us using the information in the "Contact Us" section below.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact our Privacy Officer at:
        </p>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mt-4">
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Email:</strong> privacy@medgemmahealth.com</p>
          <p class="mb-2"><strong>Phone:</strong> (800) 555-0123</p>
          <p>
            <strong>Postal Address:</strong><br>
            MedGemma Health<br>
            Attn: Privacy Officer<br>
            123 Health Avenue<br>
            San Francisco, CA 94107
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA Section -->
<section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center" data-controller="fade-in">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Still Have Questions?</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
        Our privacy team is here to help you understand how we protect your information.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-blue-600 text-white font-medium rounded-lg shadow-md hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors">
          <i class="fas fa-envelope mr-2"></i>
          Contact Us
        </a>
        <a href="/help-center" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-white border border-gray-300 text-gray-700 font-medium rounded-lg shadow-sm hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle mr-2"></i>
          Visit Help Center
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
